<item>
            <title>[STORM-2660] The Nimbus storm-local directory is relative to the working directory of the shell executing &quot;storm nimbus&quot;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/STORM-2660</link>
                <project id="12314820" key="STORM">Apache Storm</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When the storm.local.dir property is set to a relative directory, it should be interpreted as relative to STORM_HOME. This is how it works for &quot;storm supervisor&quot;. For &quot;storm nimbus&quot; it is instead relative to the working directory of the shell, so running &quot;storm nimbus&quot; from STORM_HOME/bin will put a storm-local directory in STORM_HOME/bin/storm-local.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Windows 10, Ubuntu 17.04</environment>
